sentences: Matthew (Matt) Edwards (born 4 June 1975) is an English electronic music producer and DJ based in Berlin, Germany.
He is also co-founder of London-based record label Rekids, which he formed in 2006 with James Masters.
Edwards' career began as a DJ in London and Aberystwyth, where he picked up a residency at the Milk Bar in 1992 and Aberystwyth football club.
Radio Slave began in 2000 as a duo remixing project with Serge Santiago.
Around 2002, Serge left to pursue his own musical path leaving Edwards in control of the Radio Slave guise.
He continued to produce a string of remixes for well-established artists, before finally releasing his own original material in 2006.
The music is available on CD and vinyl as The Machine's LP 'RedHead' and was released in 2010.
The second track Opening Ceremony (Fuse) also appeared on Berlin imprint Innervisions in 2009 remixed by Ame and Dixon.
As REKID, Matt released 14-track album 'Made in Menorca' in 2006 on Soul Jazz Records.
In 2011 he collaborated with Japanese toy maker Devilrobots to create a Rekids-themed toy 'No Sleep No Tofu'.
In May 2012, Edwards released a sample pack with label Sample Magic.
2012 also saw the launch the 'Pyramids of Mars' label – a multimedia project that incorporates various strands of artistic disciplines.
The 2010 album RedHead (under his 'Machine' pseudonym) was re-issued on Pyramids of Mars as part of a deluxe package, including a re-interpretation of the full album by Joe Claussell.

Edwards is consistently touring throughout the year and currently holds residencies at Berlin's Panorama Bar and Paris' Rex Club with the Rekids club nights.
In recent years, he has also released a number of different mix CDs including Fabric 48 and Strictly Rhythm Vol. 5.
